ADD precursor.311.desc:0 "Greetings from [artifact_seller.Capital.GetName]. There is a matter my government wishes to discuss.\n\nWe understand that your archeologists have been studying the ancient [Root.GetPrecursorCiv] civilization for quite some time. Understandable, since their territory once covered a large part of what today constitutes the [Root.GetName].\n\nAs it happens, their territory also extended into what is now the [artifact_seller.GetName], and [artifact_seller.GetSpeciesAdj] archeologists have recovered a number of unique artifacts. If you are interested, we would be willing to sell you one of these artifacts."
ADD precursor.311.a:0 "Expensive, but we accept."
ADD precursor.311.a.reply:0 "Excellent. We will make arrangements to transport the artifact to [Root.Capital.GetName] at once."
ADD precursor.311.b:0 "We have a counter-proposal..."
ADD precursor.311.b.reply:0 "You drive a hard bargain, but we would expect nothing less from [Root.GetSpeciesNamePlural]. We accept your offer."
ADD precursor.311.c:0 "Surrender that artifact now or suffer the consequences."
ADD precursor.311.d:0 "Not interested."
ADD precursor.312.desc:0 "The [artifact_seller.GetName] does not give in to threats. You have made new enemies this day, [Root.GetSpeciesNamePlural]!"
ADD precursor.312.d:0 "So be it."
ADD precursor.313.desc:0 "I... we... the [artifact_seller.GetName] will of course gladly donate the artifact to the [Root.GetName], in the interest of fostering amicable relations between our two star nations."
ADD precursor.313.d:0 "A wise decision."
ADD opinion_threatened_artifact:0 "Threatened Us"
ADD purchase_artifact:0 "We purchase a Precursor artifact from the [artifact_seller.GetName].\n\n"
ADD coerce_artifact:0 "We attempt to coerce the [artifact_seller.GetName] into giving us their Precursor artifact."
ADD precursor.314.desc:0 "Greetings, [Root.GetSpeciesAdj] friends.\n\nA recent [artifact_giver.GetSpeciesAdj] archeological expedition on one of our planets uncovered several artifacts believed to have originated in the ancient [Root.GetPrecursorCiv] Precursor civilization.\n\nThe artifacts are currently being displayed in a museum on [artifact_giver.Capital.GetName], but in honor of the friendship between our two great empires, the [artifact_giver.GetName] would like to donate one of the pieces to the [Root.GetName]. Arrangements have already been made to transport the artifact to [Root.Capital.GetName]."
ADD precursor.314.a:0 "Thank you for this gift."
ADD primitive.180.name:0 "[From.GetName]"
ADD primitive.180.desc:0 "Greetings. You have no doubt taken note of our ascent from humble beginnings, just as we have taken note of your $fleet_type_shipclass_starbase$ orbiting our star. We understand that this $fleet_type_shipclass_starbase$ represents some hypothetical claim on this system.\n\nWe ask only that you relinquish this hold on our space, ceding the $fleet_type_shipclass_starbase$ to the beings who have called [From.Capital.GetStarName] home since time immemorial.\n\nIt is only just."
ADD primitive.180.a:0 "Of course. It is only just."
ADD primitive.180.a.tooltip:0 "§RCede§! the §Y[From.Capital.GetStarName] $fleet_type_shipclass_starbase$§! to the §Y[From.GetName]§!\n\n§Y$opinion_ceded_starbase$§!: §Y[From.GetName]§! will hold a §Ghigher§! §HOpinion§! of §Y[Root.GetName]§!"
ADD primitive.180.b:0 "A laughable demand from an immature civilization."
ADD primitive.180.b.tooltip:0 "Keep control of the §Y[From.Capital.GetStarName] $fleet_type_shipclass_starbase$§!\n\n§Y$opinion_not_ceded_starbase$§!: §Y[From.GetName]§! will hold a §Rlower§! §HOpinion§! of §Y[Root.GetName]§!"
NEW observation.2000.desc:1 "The thousands of scientists and advisors we sent to [From.From.From.GetName] have finally completed the arduous task of bringing the local civilization up to an early Space Age level of technology. Under their new unified government, the aliens now style themselves as the "[From.From.From.Owner.GetName]" and they have agreed to become our vassals.\n\nWe have ceded full control of the system and dismantled our Observation Post, as per the conditions of our treaty with them."
OLD observation.2000.desc:0 "The thousands of scientists and advisors we sent to [From.From.From.GetName] have finally completed the arduous task of bringing the local civilization up to an early Space Age level of technology. Under their new unified government, the aliens now style themselves as the "[From.From.From.Owner.GetName]" and they have agreed to become our vassals.\n\nOur Observation Post above their homeworld has been dismantled, as per the conditions of our treaty with them."
CN  observation.2000.desc:1 "我们派往[From.From.From.GetName]的数千位科学家和顾问终于完成了任务，让当地的文明水平进步到了早期太空时代。他们建立了统一的国家，自称“[From.From.From.Owner.GetName]”，并同意成为我们的附庸。\n\n我们位于他们母星上方的的观测站已经被拆除，这也是我们和他们之间条约的一部分。"
NEW crisis.52.a.response:0 "Many Sentinels have military backgrounds. We are survivors from a dozen different fleets that fought the Prethoryn and lost. As Sentinels, we have learned from the mistakes of the past and work hard never to repeat them.\n\nAlso, I believe I mentioned that we recruit from all species in the galaxy. This includes the elder races, such as the [sentinel_fallen_empire.GetSpeciesNamePlural]. We have the support of several influential factions within the §H[sentinel_fallen_empire.GetName]§! who have no wish to see their galaxy devoured. They have donated both ships and resources to our cause."
OLD crisis.52.a.response:0 "Many Sentinels have military backgrounds. We are survivors from a dozen different fleets that fought the Prethoryn and lost. As Sentinels, we have learned from the mistakes of the past and work hard never to repeat them.\n\nAlso, I believe I mentioned that we recruit from all species in the galaxy. This includes the elder races, such as the [fallen_empire.GetSpeciesNamePlural]. We have the support of several influential factions within the [fallen_empire.GetName] who have no wish to see their galaxy devoured. They have donated both ships and resources to our cause."
CN  crisis.52.a.response:0 "很多星际护卫都有军事背景。我们都曾是与虫族战斗的各个舰队的幸存者。虽然曾经战败，但我们汲取了过去的经验与教训，并争取不再重蹈覆辙。\n\n就像之前所说过的，星际护卫队的成员来自银河系的各个种族。其中包括诸如[fallen_empire.GetSpeciesNamePlural]这种古老种族。我们还得到了[fallen_empire.GetName]的多方支援，大家都不想放任自己的星系被敌人吞噬，于是向星际护卫队提供了船只与资源方面的支持。"
NEW crisis.52.b.response:0 "For some time now we have been building up our headquarters in the §H[sentinel_system.GetName]§! system. The coordinates of this uncharted system were given to us by the [sentinel_fallen_empire.GetName], who also aided in the construction of our main base on §HSentinel Alpha§!.\n\nIt is quite a remarkable achievement, if I may say so. We have our own shipyards as well."
OLD crisis.52.b.response:0 "For some time now we have been building up our headquarters in the [sentinel_system.GetName] system. The coordinates of this uncharted system were given to us by the [fallen_empire.GetName], who also aided in the construction of our main base on Sentinel Alpha.\n\nIt is quite a remarkable achievement, if I may say so. We have our own shipyards as well."
CN  crisis.52.b.response:0 "我们正在[sentinel_system.GetName]星系建立主基地。这个隐秘的星系坐标是[fallen_empire.GetName]提供的，他们还帮助我们建设位于护卫α星上的主基地。\n\n我认为这是十分了不起的成就。同时，我们也建立了自己的造船厂。"
NEW crisis.234.desc:0 "Over the last few months, the Prethoryn Queen we captured has appeared increasingly restless and uneasy. At first, we thought it was simply missing its connection with the rest of its kind, until our Telepaths told us that it had been in communication with them, speaking of a 'Hole in the Void'.\n\nWhat it meant by this we found out only when a team of scientists researching Prethoryn intergalactic travel methods discovered a discrepancy in our astronomical database. While charting the likely path the Prethoryn had been following, they found that a small spiral galaxy some 30 million light-years distant from our own was... missing.\n\nThe galaxy, discovered and studied during the early space era of our species, is simply no longer emanating any form of light observable by our instruments. This bizarre and unexpected discovery sent our scientists into a scramble to try and explain what could cause an entire galaxy to simply vanish from the sky.\n\nTwo explanations emerged: Either the stars of the galaxy simply went out, all at once, or there is something, something so vast as to eclipse an entire galaxy, blocking its light from reaching us. Both theories seem equally implausible, and many have simply decried them as ludicrous, preferring to think that the missing galaxy never existed at all, invented by some erroneous use of a primitive telescope. Nonetheless, a palpable sense of dread and foreboding surrounds the whole incident..."
